qas.question: When did the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period of China take place?
When did the Song dynasty take place?
What dynasty was concerned with countering northern enemy states?

context: During the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period of China (<a0_0>907–960<a0_0/>), while the fractured political realm of China saw no threat in a Tibet which was in just as much political disarray, there was little in the way of Sino-Tibetan relations. Few documents involving Sino-Tibetan contacts survive from the <a2_0>Song dynasty<a2_0/> (<a1_0>960–1279<a1_0/>). The Song were far more concerned with countering northern enemy states of <a3_0>the Khitan<a3_0/>-ruled Liao dynasty (907–1125) and <a4_0>Jurchen<a4_0/>-ruled Jin dynasty (1115–1234).
